# Authentication Flow

## Current Implementation

The Kenya Health Intelligence Platform currently does not implement authentication. This document outlines the current state and future considerations.

## Current State

- **No Authentication**: The application is publicly accessible
- **No User Management**: All data is read-only static data
- **No Protected Routes**: All routes are publicly accessible

## Future Authentication Design

For future implementation with authentication:

flowchart TD
    A[User visits app] --> B{Is authenticated?}
    B -->|No| C[Show login page]
    B -->|Yes| D[Load user session]
    C --> E[User enters credentials]
    E --> F{Valid credentials?}
    F -->|No| G[Show error message]
    F -->|Yes| H[Create session]
    H --> I[Store token]
    I --> D
    D --> J[Access protected content]

## Authentication Options

### Option 1: Firebase Authentication
- Easy to implement
- Social login support
- Free tier available

### Option 2: Supabase Auth
- PostgreSQL integration
- Row-level security
- Free tier available

### Option 3: NextAuth.js
- Flexible provider support
- Session management
- Good for React apps

